It's easier to use the complement: P(at least one match) = 1 - P(no matches)

P(no matches) is the probability that no student rolls their own number. This is a derangement problem.

For n = 12 students with fair 12-sided dice:
- Total possible outcomes: 12^12
- Outcomes with no matches (derangements): D(12) × 1

The number of derangements D(n) can be calculated using:
D(n) = n! × Σ((-1)^k / k!) for k = 0 to n

Or using the formula:
D(n) = n! × Σ((-1)^k / k!) for k = 0 to n

For n = 12:
D(12) = 12! × (1 - 1/1! + 1/2! - 1/3! + 1/4! - 1/5! + 1/6! - 1/7! + 1/8! - 1/9! + 1/10! - 1/11! + 1/12!)

