Solution: I need to find P(A₁ ∪ A₂ ∪ A₃) using the inclusion-exclusion principle (Theorem 1.1-6).

The inclusion-exclusion principle states:
P(A₁ ∪ A₂ ∪ A₃) = P(A₁) + P(A₂) + P(A₃) - P(A₁ ∩ A₂) - P(A₁ ∩ A₃) - P(A₂ ∩ A₃) + P(A₁ ∩ A₂ ∩ A₃)

Given information:
- P(A₁) = P(A₂) = P(A₃) = 1/3
- P(A₁ ∩ A₂) = P(A₁ ∩ A₃) = P(A₂ ∩ A₃) = (1/3)² = 1/9
- P(A₁ ∩ A₂ ∩ A₃) = (1/3)³ = 1/27

