- $B_2$: 0 white, 2 red
- $B_3$: 2 white, 2 red
- $B_4$: 3 white, 1 red

**Selection Probabilities:**
- $P(B_1) = 1/2$
- $P(B_2) = 1/4$
- $P(B_3) = 1/8$
- $P(B_4) = 1/8$

**Probability of White Chip from Each Bowl:**
- $P(W|B_1) = 2/2 = 1$
- $P(W|B_2) = 0/2 = 0$
- $P(W|B_3) = 2/4 = 1/2$
- $P(W|B_4) = 3/4$

**Using the Law of Total Probability:**

$$P(W) = P(W|B_1)P(B_1) + P(W|B_2)P(B_2) + P(W|B_3)P(B_3) + P(W|B_4)P(B_4)$$

